3. To generate or disseminate false information with the purpose of harming others.
4. To generate or disseminate personally identifiable information that can be used to harm an individual.
5. To defame, disparage or otherwise harass others.
6. For any use intended to or which has the effect of harming individuals or groups based on social behavior or personality characteristics.
7. For any use intended to or which has the effect of discriminating against individuals or groups.
8. To impersonate any person or entity or otherwise misrepresent affiliation, including creating synthetic speech emulating or similar to a specific natural person.
9. To detect or infer aspects/features of an identity of any natural persons (such as name, gender, sexual orientation, race, religion, age, location, health/medical conditions).

